      "content": "thanks for that. we don't have a full-blown OS with Valgrind or anything like that on this specific chip, it's pretty barebones. we basically only have a basic heap monitor that shows total free bytes. \n\nif i can't use heavy profiling tools, how can i narrow down which specific module or subsystem is responsible? is there a way to implement some kind of lightweight \"canary\" or tracking system within the code itself without blowing out the memory even more?",
